TSX-listed Orvana Minerals has restarted operations and production at its Orovalle gold/copper/silver mine, in Spain, after a nationwide truck driversâ€™ strike came to an end on Saturday. The transport strike started on March 14, causing a significant disruption to supply chains. Orvana reported on Monday that it had received the required materials to restart operations. The miner would provide a comprehensive update on the impact of the temporary stoppage as part of the second-quarter reporting process.